    <section>
      <title>Different inflection classes</title>

      <p>Finite verb inflection is determined by the class the individual verb is a member of. There
        are some indicators that help identifying inflection classes, such as the type of stem a
        verb has by counting the number of syllables in the final foot of the word. A <em
          class="focus">foot</em> is a group of syllables where the first syllable has stress. Here
        the syllables are separated with a hyphen "-", and the foot is marked with parentheses "()".
        Stress is marked with ' before the syllable.</p>

    </section>

